Session of 2025
SENATE BILL No. 2
By Senators Blew and Clifford
1-8
1 AN ACT concerning school districts; relating to question submitted
2 elections on the issuance of bonds by a school district; validating the
3 election results for the bond issuance question submitted by the board
4 of education of USD 200, Greeley county.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. The result of the election held on May 21, 2024, on the
8 question submitted by the board of education of unified school district no.
9 200, Greeley county, for the purpose of authorizing the issuance of general
10 obligation bonds in an amount not to exceed $4,600,000 to pay the costs
11 to: (a) Construct, furnish, equip and acquire improvements, additions and
12 renovations to the school district's elementary and junior/senior high
13 school facility, including safety and security improvements, playground
14 improvements, locker room additions and renovations, a gymnasium
15 addition and improvements to comply with the Americans with disabilities
16 act; (b) construct, furnish, equip and acquire other necessary renovations
17 and improvements to school district facilities; (c) make all other necessary
18 improvements appurtenant thereto; and (d) pay the costs of issuance and
19 interest on the bonds during construction of the project is hereby declared
20 valid, and the board of education may issue such general obligation bonds
21 as otherwise provided by law in an amount not to exceed $4,600,000 for
22 the purposes specified herein.
23 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
24 publication in the Kansas register.

